This is a list of important participants in [[Muslim feminism]], originally sorted by surname within each period.
It may include, for instance, earlier authors who did not self-identify as feminists but have been claimed to have furthered "feminist consciousness" by a resistance of male dominance expressed in their works. <!-- Please insert alphabetically by surname within each period. --> <!-- Please put country of main activity or residence first (for sorting) --> <!-- Reliable sources should be added in order to establish notability as important participant in the development of feminism -->
