atribune.com/bangladesh/2014/dec/08/begum-rokeya-day-tomorrow |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |accessdate=25 June 2016}}</ref> |- |1875–1939||data-sort-value="Shaarawi, Huda"|[[Huda Sha'arawi]]||Egypt||1879||1947||organiser; founder of [[Egyptian Feminist Union]]||<ref>Shaʻrāwī, Hudá, and Margot Badran. Harem years: the memoirs of an Egyptian feminist (1879-1924). New York: Feminist Press at the City University of New York, 1987.</ref> |- |1875-1939||data-sort-value="Salem, Hidaya Sultan al-"|[[Hidaya Sultan al-Salem]]||Kuwait||1936||2001||writer, campaigner, suffragist||<ref name=irishtimes>{{cite news|title=Magazine owner assassinated |publisher=Irish Times |date= March 21, 2001 |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/news/magazine-owner-assassinated-1.292922}}</ref><ref name=foreignpolicy>{{cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2012/07/01/arab-secularism-and-its-discontents/|title=Arab secularism and its discontents|work=Foreign Policy}}</ref> |- |1875-1939||data-sort-value="Said, Rasuna"|[[Rasuna Said]]||Indonesia||1910||1965||political leader, nationalist||<ref>Tim Gabung Ilmu, ''Pahlawan Indonesia & profilnya: edisi terlengkap [Profiles of Indonesian heroes; complete edition], Gedung Ilmu, Jakarta, {{ISBN|978 602 9080 30 8}}.</ref> |- |1875-1939||data-sort-value="Nabarawi, Saiza"|[[Saiza Nabarawi]]||Eqypt||1897||1985||journalist||<ref>Chaudhry, Ayesha S. ''women'', in Bulliet, Richard, David Cook, Roxanne L. Euben, Khaled Fahmy, Frank Griffel, Bernard Haykel, Robert W. Hefner, Timur Kuran, Jane McAuliffe, and Ebrahim Moosa. [https://muse.jhu.edu/book/30637 The Princeton Encyclopedia of Islamic Political Thought]. Princeton University Press, 2012. p 598, via [[Wikipedia:Project MUSE]]. (Subscription required)</ref> |- |1937-2003||data-sort-value="Sobhan, Salma"|[[Salma Sobhan]]||Bangladesh||1937||2003||lawyer, academic||<ref name="Banglapedia">{{cite book | title = Banglapedia: National Encyclopedia of Bangladesh | chapter = Sobhan, Salma | author = Hameeda Hossain | editor1 