{{Notability|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox video game |title = The Political Machine 2016 |image = |developer = [[Stardock]] |publisher = |designer = |engine = |released = February 4, 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politicalmachine.com/|title=The Political Machine 2016|work=|first=|last=|date=January 26, 2016|accessdate=January 26, 2016}}</ref> |genre = [[Government simulation game|Government simulation]] |modes = [[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]] }}
'''''The Political Machine 2016''''' is a [[government simulation game]] from [[Stardock]] and the fourth game in the ''[[The Political Machine (series)|Political Machine]]'' series, in which the player leads a [[election campaign|campaign]] to elect the [[President of the United States]]. The player accomplishes this goal by traveling from state to state and engaging in a variety of activities to either raise money or raise [[Opinion poll|poll]] numbers. An [[early access]] version of the game was released on [[Steam (software)|Steam]] on November 17, 2015, with the full game releasing on February 4, 2016.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2015/11/23/the-political-machine-2016-review-early-access/ | title=Premature Evaluation: The Political Machine 2016 | work=[[Rock, Paper, Shotgun]] | first=Marsh | last=Davies | date=November 23, 2015 | accessdate=January 26, 2016}}</ref>
==Reception== {{Video game reviews | MC = 72/100<ref name=MC>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/the-political-machine-2016 |title=The Political Machine 2016 for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=May 9, 2016}}</ref> }}
The game received "average" reviews according to video game [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=MC/>
